The paper discusses the design and evaluation of search heuristics for constraint programming, which is a subfield of artificial intelligence (cs.AI). The algorithms proposed in the paper involve counting the number of solutions to specific families of constraints, which suggests a focus on data structures and algorithms (cs.DS). The paper also discusses the experimental evaluation of the proposed heuristics, which involves analyzing and interpreting data, suggesting a focus on machine learning (cs.LG). Additionally, the paper discusses the design of algorithms and heuristics, which suggests a focus on programming languages (cs.PL) and software engineering (cs.SE).
